metadata.description: Query Database of SMS, Contacts etc
The App logs information. Sensitive information should never be logged.
metadata.cwe: CWE-532 Insertion of Sensitive Information into Log File
CWE-327 Use of a Broken or Risky Cryptographic Algorithm
metadata.description: SHA-1 is a weak hash known to have hash collisions.
This App copies data to clipboard. Sensitive data should not be copied to clipboard as other applications can access it.
App creates temp file. Sensitive information should never be written into a temp file.
App uses SQLite Database and execute raw SQL query. Untrusted user input in raw SQL queries can cause SQL Injection. Also sensitive information should be encrypted and written to the database.
metadata.cwe: CWE-89 Improper Neutralization of Special Elements used in an SQL Command ('SQL Injection')
CWE-312 Cleartext Storage of Sensitive Information
metadata.description: Files may contain hardcoded sensitive informations like usernames, passwords, keys etc.
The App uses an insecure Random Number Generator.
metadata.cwe: CWE-330 Use of Insufficiently Random Values

metadata.description: This App uses SQL Cipher. SQLCipher provides 256-bit AES encryption to sqlite database files.
The App uses ECB mode in Cryptographic encryption algorithm. ECB mode is known to be weak as it results in the same ciphertext for identical blocks of plaintext.
metadata.cwe: CWE-327 Use of a Broken or Risky Cryptographic Algorithm

playstore_details.title: BitGuard Blockchain Wallet
playstore_details.description:
What is BitGuard?

BitGuard is an un-hackable, multi chain and decentralised cryptocurrency soft wallet.

BitGuard’s hardware wallet will be launched soon.


Why BitGuard?

Crypto wallets are as secure as the owner's private key's location. 

If your tokens are on exchanges, they are not your tokens. Exchanges are extremely prone to hacks. If you have kept your private keys on third party apps, they are even more prone to attacks. Is it really worth taking the risk with your money?

With BitGuard, the private key never leaves your app's ecosystem, hence making it impossible to steal. With added extra layer of pin authentication, your wallet is impossible to crack. Take control of your decentralised token.

When you keep your tokens in BitGuard, only you control them. Not even the developers of BitGuard have access to your keys. Moreover, you are presented with mnemonic code which you can use to recover your tokens anywhere, anytime and from any HD wallet application (including BitGuard).

Feature:

* Create new wallet or import existing wallet.
* Secure Private Keys with frontend signing.
* Keys never leave the wallet application.
* Receive and Send funds in a click.
* Instant transaction updates.
* One mnemonics to control them all

Tokens Supported:

* Bitcoin
* Ethereum
* Litecoin
* Dogecoin
* DASH
* ALL ERC20 like KNC, 0x, DRGN, OST etc.

For any more token support requests, please mail at info@blockwala.io

Join our telegram channel https://t.me/joinchat/GnFBJgw8Rz00CIMjhCnK1g
Pre-order our hardware wallet here: www.bitguard-wallet.com
Privacy policy: https://blockwala.io/privacypolicy.htm
